text: 35000 is the number of genes in a human being.
1501 is the year that the Banquet of Chestnuts is held by Cesare Borgia in the Papal Palace of Rome on October 30th.
1501 is the year that Copernicus is formally installed as canon of Frauenberg Cathedral on July 27th.
1501 is the year that Ismail I is enthroned as Shah of Azerbaijan, choosing Tabriz as his capital, founding the Safavid dynasty in northern Iran on July NaNth.
1501 is the year that Amerigo Vespucci discovers and names Baía de Todos os Santos in Brazil on November (All Saints) 1st.
1729 is the smallest natural number representable in two different ways as a sum of two positive cubes, as Ramanujan stated on the spot.
January 30th is the day in 1703 that the Forty-seven Ronin, under the command of Ōishi Kuranosuke, avenge the death of their master.
